  {
    "page": 3,
    "block_id": "page_003:block_050",
    "block_type": "text",
    "text": "CaVulner : Automated Context-Aware Identification of Vulnerable Versions 3",
    "bbox": [
      45.827999114990234,
      60.60470199584961,
      440.1680908203125,
      69.88189697265625
    ],
    "reading_order": 50,
    "column_guess": null,
    "confidence": "medium"
  },
  {
    "page": 3,
    "block_id": "page_003:block_051",
    "block_type": "text",
    "text": "• We propose a novel LLM - driven vulnerable version identification approach, CaVulner , which integrates multi-source context and leverages the capabilities of LLMs in vulnerability analysis and code understanding. The evaluation results demonstrate that CaVulner significantly outper- forms state-of-the-art methods including V-SZZ, VERJava and LLM4SZZ. It achieves at least a 35.80% improvement in accuracy at the CVE level. At the version level, precision increases by at least 10.40%, recall by 14.59% and F1-score by 23.94%.",
    "bbox": [
      45.8280029296875,
      83.43697357177734,
      441.8560791015625,
      156.98141479492188
    ],
    "reading_order": 51,
    "column_guess": null,
    "confidence": "medium"
  },
  {
    "page": 3,
    "block_id": "page_003:block_052",
    "block_type": "text",
    "text": "• We manually audited all 176 CVEs and identified the vulnerable versions, constructing a high- quality ground truth dataset containing 17,436 of these.",
    "bbox": [
      45.8280029296875,
      155.1680450439453,
      441.853515625,
      180.89138793945312
    ],
    "reading_order": 52,
    "column_guess": null,
    "confidence": "medium"
  },
  {
    "page": 3,
    "block_id": "page_003:block_053",
    "block_type": "text",
    "text": "• We have released CaVulner and related experiment datasets on our website [ 1 ] to facilitate further research.",
    "bbox": [
      45.8280029296875,
      179.0780792236328,
      440.36474609375,
      204.80239868164062
    ],
    "reading_order": 53,
    "column_guess": null,
    "confidence": "medium"
  },
  {
    "page": 3,
    "block_id": "page_003:block_054",
    "block_type": "text",
    "text": "2 Preliminaries In this section, we introduce the concepts of vulnerability-inducing commit, and a motivating example.",
    "bbox": [
      45.827999114990234,
      212.97125244140625,
      440.1689147949219,
      252.62240600585938
    ],
    "reading_order": 54,
    "column_guess": null,
    "confidence": "medium"
  },
  {
    "page": 3,
